The governor of Plateau, Simon Lalong, has urged Nigerians to support candidates who are God-fearing and have respect for humanity, in their quest for public offices. The governor made the call at the General Assembly of Catholics in Politics and Catholic Business Leaders in Abuja as contained in a statement by his Director of Press and Public Affairs, Dr. Makut Macham, on Friday in Jos He said the godly principles will guide them in their discharge of duties, where justice and good governance will be given a high premium. He urged Nigerians of all religious faiths to fully participate in all the Countryâ€™s electoral processes, to facilitate national rebirth where the aspirations of Nigeria can be achieved. Lalong described the event as significant in providing a platform for Catholic politicians and captains of industry to reflect on their roles in ensuring the progress of Nigeria. He said the event was also a good forum to discuss the various challenges confronting Nigeria which include insecurity, corruption, diseases, poverty, and poor infrastructure with a view of seeking solutions to facilitate improvement. 